  <title translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups Dialog Box</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">confined</keyword>
    <keyword translate="true">convertible</keyword>
    <keyword translate="true">quasi-3D</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to define the layer structure of a MODFLOW model. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is displayed by selecting</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Layer Groups...</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In the Layer Property Flow package in MODFLOW, layers can be either confined or convertible. &#160;Cells in convertible layers will either be confined or unconfined depending on whether the head is above or below the top of the cell. &#160;In addition, it is possible to have quasi-3-D models in which there is a gap between the layers. &#160;In such cases, the vertical hydraulic conductivity of the missing material is used to help calculate the conductance between the layers. &#160;Both the missing material and the model layers are represented in ModelMuse by layer groups. &#160;Layer group that represent model layers can be subdivided into multiple layers. &#160;This can simplify the process of defining layers when it is important to simulate vertical flow within an aquifer or if solute transport is simulated. More typically, however, each aquifer in the model will be represented by a single layer. &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To define the layer structure of a MODFLOW model, the user adds or removes layer groups using the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Add layer group </text><image src="AddLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Add Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Insert layer group</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="InsertLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Insert Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Delete layer group </text><image src="DeleteLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Delete Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> buttons on the left hand side of &#160;the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The main properties of each the layer group is specified by selecting the layer group in the list of layer groups on the left and entering appropriate values on the tabs to the right. The user can select multiple layer groups by holding down the Ctrl key when selecting layer groups.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box has two tabs that are always visible, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Basics_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Basics</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab and the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Discretization_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Discretization</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab. &#160;If the &#160;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SUB_Subsidence_and_Aquifer_Sys" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SUB</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">package is active, two more tabs, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="No_Delay_Beds_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">No-Delay Beds</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Delay_Beds_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Delay Beds</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tabs, are visible. If the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SWT_Package" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWT</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SWT_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWT</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab is visible. If the Dispersion package in MT3DMS is selected, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Dispersion_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Dispersion</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab is visible.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
